<p><b>Bridget Louise Riley</b> <a href="/wiki/Order_of_the_Companions_of_Honour" title="Order of the Companions of Honour">CH</a> <a href="/wiki/Order_of_the_British_Empire" title="Order of the British Empire">CBE</a> (born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1931-04-24"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="04-24"><a href="/wiki/April_24" title="April 24">April 24</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1931" title="1931">1931</a></span> in <a href="/wiki/West_Norwood" title="West Norwood">Norwood</a><sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>, <a href="/wiki/London" title="London">London</a>) is an <a href="/wiki/England" title="England">English</a> <a href="/wiki/Painting" title="Painting">painter</a> who is one of the foremost proponents of <a href="/wiki/Op_art" title="Op art">op art</a>.</p>
